<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-09T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-09T08:00:00-05:00" n="816" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">895.6463/11–945: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-09T16:00:00+03:00">November 9, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received November 9—11:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3809. Department’s 2304, November 7. Removal by Soviet authorities of
                                equipment from Yalu River power plants.</p>
                            <p>I wrote to Vyshinski<note n="24" xml:id="d816fn1">Audrey Yanuaryevich
                                    Vyshinsky, People’s Vice Commissar for Foreign Affairs of the
                                    Soviet Union.</note> on November 8 making representations on
                                this case.</p>
                            <p>Department, please repeat to Tokyo and Seoul.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>